comments: Dunn (UTA) brings his hands to the ball and cleanly deflects it away from Daniels (NOP) during his drive into the paint.
Daniels (NOP) goes to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal lower body contact occurs with Kessler (UTA) as Daniels secures the ball.
Kessler (UTA) establishes himself in a wide screening position and contact occurs with Jones (NOP), causing him to collide with Markkanen (UTA) as the screen is set.
Kessler (UTA) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact with Nance Jr. (NOP during the dunk attempt at the basket.
Murphy III (NOP) makes contact with the part of Markkanen's (UTA) left hand that is off of the ball during his release, affecting the jump shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) establishes himself in Sexton's (UTA) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Collins (UTA) reaches in for the ball and makes contact with Williamson's (NOP) arm, which affects his layup attempt at the basket.
Jones (NOP) rests his forearm on Collins' (UTA) back and marginal contact occurs as Jones releases away from the defender during the rebounding opportunity.
Collins (UTA) rests and removes his hand from Jones' (NOP) left arm and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Williamson's (NOP) left hand makes last contact with the ball prior to it falling out of bounds. Possession should have been awarded to Utah.
Williamson (NOP) establishes himself in Sexton's (UTA) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Sexton (UTA) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Markkanen (UTA) firms up in Ingram's (NOP) path and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs while setting the screen.
Jones (NOP) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Sexton (UTA) goes over the screen and marginal contact occurs as he comes together with Jones (NOP).
Nance Jr. (NOP) brings his hand toward the ball and Markkanen (UTA) spins away from the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Nance Jr. (NOP) does not beat Markkanen (UTA) to the spot and the offensive player spins away from the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Williamson (NOP) lowers his arm down and makes contact with Markkanen's (UTA) arm, which affects his shot attempt in the paint.
Sexton (UTA) moves to, rather than through, Ingram's (NOP) space and marginal body contact occurs.
Williamson (NOP) firms up in Sexton's (UTA) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Williamson (NOP) comes together with Sexton (UTA), while he is setting the screen, and marginal contact occurs.

McCollum (NOP) engages with Dunn (UTA) as both players move toward the paint and the contact is marginal. Dunn then makes incidental foot to foot contact with his teammate, Sexton (UTA), and stumbles toward the baseline.
Nance Jr. (NOP) and Sexton (UTA) come together while pursuing the loose ball and the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Nance Jr. (NOP) makes last contact with the ball. Possession is properly awarded to Utah.
